WEBVTT

00:01.120 --> 00:03.580
Previously on "Emergence"...
Cancer's back.

00:03.580 --> 00:04.710
We did this before.
We can do it again.

00:04.710 --> 00:05.920
Not this time, honey.

00:05.920 --> 00:08.000
Telling an AI
it's an AI

00:08.000 --> 00:09.920
effectively destroys
the program.

00:09.920 --> 00:11.040
Wouldn't that be like
killing her?

00:11.040 --> 00:12.170
Better her than us.

00:12.170 --> 00:14.620
Ryan Brooks.
I'm with the FBI.

00:14.620 --> 00:16.210
Everything they're
investigating leads to Piper.

00:18.790 --> 00:20.170
You wanted to get
to Emily first.

00:20.170 --> 00:21.210
Why?

00:21.210 --> 00:22.580
She's in
federal custody now.

00:22.580 --> 00:24.830
Really looking forward
to hearing what she has to say.

00:24.830 --> 00:27.170
You took what didn't
belong to you, Alan.

00:27.170 --> 00:28.500
I'll get it back.
[ Blade plunges ]

00:31.500 --> 00:32.880
Piper wants to
open her present.

00:32.880 --> 00:33.750
I didn't get her a present.

00:33.750 --> 00:35.040
Yeah, I saw it.

00:35.040 --> 00:36.580
"To Piper, from 'Mom.'"

00:36.580 --> 00:37.750
Piper!
No, Jo. No, no, no.
No, no, no!

00:39.500 --> 00:41.290
It told me
who I am.

00:43.000 --> 00:45.750
[ Sharon Van Etten's
"Memorial Day" plays ]

00:45.750 --> 00:52.120
♪♪

00:52.120 --> 00:57.620
♪ Where do you always stay? ♪

00:57.620 --> 01:00.540
♪ Where do you stay? ♪

01:00.540 --> 01:02.830
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

01:02.830 --> 01:07.330
Yes. It's done.
♪ When you look ♪

01:07.330 --> 01:08.880
No.

01:08.880 --> 01:12.380
There is nothing
left to do here.

01:12.380 --> 01:15.500
Guess I'm on my way
to Long Island.

01:15.500 --> 01:23.710
♪♪

01:23.710 --> 01:29.080
♪♪

01:29.080 --> 01:34.710
♪♪

01:34.710 --> 01:37.080
Mia: Now right.

01:37.080 --> 01:39.330
Now up.

01:39.330 --> 01:41.790
Down.

01:41.790 --> 01:44.120
They look normal.

01:44.120 --> 01:46.710
Good.

01:46.710 --> 01:48.920
Did it hurt?

01:48.920 --> 01:50.210
I don't think so.

01:50.210 --> 01:52.210
Was it scary?

01:54.880 --> 01:56.830
It was.

01:56.830 --> 01:59.210
But then it wasn't.

02:02.290 --> 02:05.580
Everything's
different now.

02:05.580 --> 02:11.790
♪♪

02:11.790 --> 02:14.790
Feels the same to me.

02:14.790 --> 02:20.170
♪♪

02:20.170 --> 02:22.960
Yeah,
I don't believe it.

02:22.960 --> 02:25.170
I know what I saw.

02:25.170 --> 02:26.500
But I can't --
I can't believe this.

02:26.500 --> 02:27.580
Come on now. What are you
trying to tell me?

02:27.580 --> 02:29.420
That she's -- she's...

02:32.420 --> 02:34.170
That's crazy.

02:34.170 --> 02:36.170
Jo, that's --
that's crazy.

02:36.170 --> 02:39.380
I examined her.

02:39.380 --> 02:41.290
She had a head CT.

02:41.290 --> 02:43.120
I know.

02:43.120 --> 02:45.670
So when she was
at the hospital,

02:45.670 --> 02:47.830
it wasn't anything we did
that saved her.

02:47.830 --> 02:52.170
No, it was
something like that.

02:52.170 --> 02:54.960
What is this?

02:54.960 --> 02:56.540
[ Sighs ]

02:56.540 --> 02:58.670
An exabyte disc,
I'm told.

02:58.670 --> 02:59.790
There's no such thing.

03:06.120 --> 03:07.580
Must've come from Emily.

03:07.580 --> 03:09.330
Why?

03:09.330 --> 03:12.040
Uh, they told me
that if she knew,

03:12.040 --> 03:15.040
if Piper found out
what she was

03:15.040 --> 03:17.960
that it would
destroy the...

03:17.960 --> 03:19.120
program.

03:19.120 --> 03:20.750
It would kill her,
essentially.

03:20.750 --> 03:22.960
But it didn't.

03:22.960 --> 03:25.540
Why not?

03:25.540 --> 03:29.620
I think because...

03:29.620 --> 03:32.080
Piper made it not happen.

03:34.540 --> 03:37.170
I always wondered
what we'd do

03:37.170 --> 03:39.420
when her real family
showed up.

03:39.420 --> 03:41.420
Just figured there would be
somebody out there

03:41.420 --> 03:43.380
who'd come get her.

03:43.380 --> 03:46.170
That's never gonna happen now,
is it?

03:46.170 --> 03:48.620
No, Dad, it's not.

03:48.620 --> 03:49.670
So what do we do?

03:49.670 --> 03:51.420
[ Door opens ]

03:51.420 --> 03:54.830
I can see you all
whispering in here.

03:54.830 --> 03:56.710
Piper and I talked.

03:56.710 --> 03:58.500
Nothing's different.

03:58.500 --> 04:01.210
So you guys have to get your
heads straight starting now.

04:01.210 --> 04:03.750
Got it?

04:03.750 --> 04:05.500
[ Clears throat ]

04:05.500 --> 04:06.830
Yeah, hon. Got it.

04:06.830 --> 04:08.790
Good. Piper's tired.

04:08.790 --> 04:11.080
We're going to bed.

04:13.000 --> 04:14.880
[ Ed chuckles ] Well, in case
anybody was wondering

04:14.880 --> 04:18.580
what Jo was like at that age,
Exhibit A.

04:18.580 --> 04:21.250
Yeah, we've still got
a party to clean up.

04:23.790 --> 04:25.880
Thanks, Abbs.

04:29.500 --> 04:32.210
♪♪

04:32.210 --> 04:36.460
[ Sighs ]

04:36.460 --> 04:39.120
You know, for what it's worth,
I don't believe it, either.

04:39.120 --> 04:42.380
Everyone tells me
that she's code,

04:42.380 --> 04:47.250
that she's a machine,
but...

04:47.250 --> 04:50.040
that's just not
what I see.

04:50.040 --> 04:51.880
It's not
what any of us see.

04:54.250 --> 04:56.620
So, I can't explain it.

04:59.330 --> 05:01.250
But we're not wrong.

05:01.250 --> 05:11.000
♪♪

05:11.000 --> 05:14.580
[ Door opens, closes ]

05:14.580 --> 05:23.580
♪♪

05:23.580 --> 05:32.830
♪♪

05:32.830 --> 05:35.670
You okay?

05:35.670 --> 05:37.920
Just looking.

05:37.920 --> 05:39.620
[ Water shuts off ]

05:39.620 --> 05:41.830
At what?

05:41.830 --> 05:44.040
To see if I can tell.

05:46.380 --> 05:49.120
[ Sighs ]

05:52.080 --> 05:53.920
I can't.

05:56.000 --> 05:59.580
You knew.

05:59.580 --> 06:00.920
Yeah.

06:00.920 --> 06:03.120
But you didn't tell me.

06:05.880 --> 06:07.960
I couldn't,
because --

06:07.960 --> 06:11.210
I know why.

06:11.210 --> 06:14.880
I'm sorry.

06:14.880 --> 06:16.880
I-It's alright.

06:19.120 --> 06:22.750
I didn't tell you something,
too.

06:25.500 --> 06:27.750
Okay.

06:27.750 --> 06:30.880
[ Sighs ]

06:30.880 --> 06:32.790
When I first got here,

06:32.790 --> 06:34.580
I took a sharp knife

06:34.580 --> 06:39.380
and I cut something
out of my neck.

06:39.380 --> 06:42.670
What?

06:42.670 --> 06:46.000
Oh, my...

06:46.000 --> 06:48.290
What was it?

06:48.290 --> 06:51.880
I don't know.

06:51.880 --> 06:56.330
But it was telling me to leave
here, and I didn't want to.

06:59.750 --> 07:01.580
Okay.

07:01.580 --> 07:04.460
Well...

07:04.460 --> 07:07.580
Is there anything else
talking to you?

07:07.580 --> 07:11.000
No.
Not right now.

07:11.000 --> 07:14.380
Not right now.
Okay.

07:14.380 --> 07:17.250
Um...

07:17.250 --> 07:19.540
Moving forward,

07:19.540 --> 07:23.080
no cutting things
out of your body.

07:23.080 --> 07:24.880
Okay?

07:24.880 --> 07:26.960
Or anyone else's body.

07:26.960 --> 07:28.540
In fact,
you know what?

07:28.540 --> 07:31.330
How about just a general
no-knives policy

07:31.330 --> 07:33.330
is what we're going for.

07:33.330 --> 07:35.620
Okay.
Okay.

07:35.620 --> 07:37.290
Alright.

07:37.290 --> 07:40.210
Uh, come on.
Go to bed.

07:42.620 --> 07:45.380
Jo?
Hmm?

07:45.380 --> 07:49.380
Most people would have
made me go away.

07:49.380 --> 07:52.080
But not you.

07:52.080 --> 07:55.670
Nope. Not me.

07:55.670 --> 08:01.210
♪♪

08:01.210 --> 08:06.420
♪♪

08:10.460 --> 08:12.920
By the time I woke up,
it was nighttime.

08:12.920 --> 08:15.500
I'm sorry.
He could be anywhere by now.

08:15.500 --> 08:17.830
You know, Wilkis disappearing
might actually do us a favor.

08:17.830 --> 08:21.040
Not like the FBI's gonna get out
of our lives any time soon.

08:21.040 --> 08:23.500
Did you
go see a doctor?

08:23.500 --> 08:25.290
That's a really long time
to be knocked out.

08:25.290 --> 08:27.710
Oh, I'm fine.
Got a hard head.

08:27.710 --> 08:31.080
Wilkis was really unraveling,
Jo.

08:31.080 --> 08:33.420
He's terrified
of Piper.

08:33.420 --> 08:35.460
Tried to task me
with killing her.

08:35.460 --> 08:37.750
Well, Emily already tried that.
It didn't work.

08:37.750 --> 08:40.460
Somehow,
Piper was able to

08:40.460 --> 08:43.000
overcome
the fatal exception error.

08:43.000 --> 08:45.080
How?

08:45.080 --> 08:46.580
[ Knock on door ]

08:46.580 --> 08:49.210
So. Weirdos in masks.
Want to hear about them?

08:49.210 --> 08:51.040
So much.

08:51.040 --> 08:52.750
I couldn't find anything
in our database,

08:52.750 --> 08:54.120
but I think
your guys might be

08:54.120 --> 08:56.540
a cyber terrorist group
called Splinter.

08:56.540 --> 08:58.710
Okay.

08:58.710 --> 09:01.500
This -- This is just a --
a Reddit forum, though.

09:01.500 --> 09:04.040
Everything I've found
has been anecdotal.

09:04.040 --> 09:07.920
Um...people in black masks
targeting big tech outfits.

09:07.920 --> 09:09.460
But, yeah,
blowing up buildings

09:09.460 --> 09:10.960
would definitely be
a new tactic.

09:10.960 --> 09:12.120
You heard of them?

09:12.120 --> 09:13.500
Never.

09:13.500 --> 09:15.710
They sound like some sort of
urban legend to me.

09:15.710 --> 09:17.420
I saw them.

09:17.420 --> 09:19.580
Even so, they're after Augur.
Not you.

09:19.580 --> 09:20.920
No.
They're after Piper.

09:20.920 --> 09:22.330
They have to be.

09:22.330 --> 09:24.540
Hey, Chief, uh,
Agent Brooks on the horn.

09:24.540 --> 09:25.710
Says it's important.

09:25.710 --> 09:26.790
I'm unavailable.

09:31.540 --> 09:33.330
I'm busy.

09:33.330 --> 09:35.460
Just from
personal experience,

09:35.460 --> 09:38.710
you can't ghost the FBI.

09:38.710 --> 09:40.420
Yeah, I know that.

09:40.420 --> 09:42.920
But I don't have to
make it easy for him, either.

09:42.920 --> 09:45.670
Uh, so, what is the plan

09:45.670 --> 09:48.080
if Emily spills her guts to him
about Piper?

09:50.750 --> 09:53.120
I'm working on it.

09:56.080 --> 09:57.380
Hey, Doc.

09:57.380 --> 09:59.830
Hi.
How are you holding up?

09:59.830 --> 10:01.620
Oh, just trying to roll with it,
you know?

10:01.620 --> 10:03.420
How about you?

10:03.420 --> 10:05.790
Been going over whatever records
I have on Piper.

10:05.790 --> 10:07.750
And?
And nothing.

10:07.750 --> 10:12.830
I mean, vitals are normal,
labs are normal.

10:12.830 --> 10:14.580
Nothing
that would explain

10:14.580 --> 10:16.620
whatever it was
we saw last night.

10:16.620 --> 10:19.080
Ah.

10:19.080 --> 10:21.000
What are you
doing here?

10:21.000 --> 10:24.040
Uh, well, I'm looking for you,
actually.

10:24.040 --> 10:26.210
What do you know
about clinical trials?

10:26.210 --> 10:28.380
Now, see.

10:28.380 --> 10:30.040
Don't --
Don't get excited.

10:30.040 --> 10:31.540
It's just a question,
Abby.

10:31.540 --> 10:33.750
Fine. Fine.

10:33.750 --> 10:36.460
Um, what kind of
clinical trials?

10:36.460 --> 10:38.330
Well, my doc called
and said that she thinks

10:38.330 --> 10:41.710
I might qualify for
some kind of gene-therapy thing.

10:41.710 --> 10:45.420
Well, everything I've read
has been really promising.

10:45.420 --> 10:46.880
It's worth
talking to them.

10:46.880 --> 10:50.000
Alright. I'm meeting the rep
in a couple minutes, so...

10:50.000 --> 10:52.120
Hey! Come on. Don't.

10:52.120 --> 10:54.620
Cut that out.
I-I can't help it.

10:54.620 --> 10:55.880
Just get whatever
data they have.

10:55.880 --> 10:57.460
I'll look it over.

10:57.460 --> 11:00.830
Okay.
Between us, right?

11:00.830 --> 11:02.250
Oh, yeah, yeah.

11:02.250 --> 11:04.000
Thank you.

11:04.000 --> 11:05.170
[ Clicks tongue ]

11:05.170 --> 11:13.960
♪♪

11:13.960 --> 11:16.040
[ Sighs ]

11:19.880 --> 11:21.000
Mr. Sawyer?

11:21.000 --> 11:22.380
Yeah, that's me.

11:22.380 --> 11:24.620
Oh,
you can call me Ed.

11:24.620 --> 11:27.580
It is so good
to meet you, Ed.

11:27.580 --> 11:28.500
I'm Helen.

11:31.960 --> 11:35.170
[ Chuckling ] I mean, this all
seems too good to be true.

11:35.170 --> 11:37.500
Five years ago,
I would've agreed with you.

11:37.500 --> 11:40.710
But with all the technological
advances we've seen,

11:40.710 --> 11:42.210
we're in a new world.

11:44.210 --> 11:47.210
[ Sighs ] Okay.
What are the side effects?

11:47.210 --> 11:51.210
Nothing.
No known side effects.

11:51.210 --> 11:53.830
Ah. Now I know
it's too good to be true.

11:53.830 --> 11:55.460
It's not.

11:55.460 --> 11:56.960
With chemotherapy,

11:56.960 --> 12:02.540
your five-year outcome is...
48%.

12:02.540 --> 12:04.290
Yeah.

12:04.290 --> 12:06.170
A little less
than a coin flip.

12:08.830 --> 12:11.040
With this treatment,

12:11.040 --> 12:16.710
your outcome jumps
to 96%.

12:16.710 --> 12:22.580
This is not about
delaying death.

12:22.580 --> 12:25.040
This is a cure.

12:25.040 --> 12:27.960
And I do not
use that word lightly.

12:27.960 --> 12:31.880
A year from now,
it's over.

12:31.880 --> 12:35.920
♪♪

12:35.920 --> 12:38.170
I really want
to believe you.

12:38.170 --> 12:40.120
You'd be a fool
not to.

12:42.750 --> 12:46.830
Okay, so, um...
say I was interested.

12:46.830 --> 12:50.120
Uh, how does my insurance work
with all this?

12:50.120 --> 12:52.920
I am sure
we can come up with

12:52.920 --> 12:58.380
a mutually beneficial
arrangement.

12:58.380 --> 13:01.290
Mia: So, the sum of
the interior angles

13:01.290 --> 13:04.960
would be 180 times 4,
right?

13:04.960 --> 13:08.670
Because there are four triangles
inside of the polygon.

13:08.670 --> 13:09.580
Get it?

13:09.580 --> 13:11.040
Yep.

13:13.290 --> 13:15.790
No.

13:15.790 --> 13:16.710
Hey.
Hey.

13:16.710 --> 13:18.040
How's it going?

13:18.040 --> 13:19.880
I'm trying to
teach Piper geometry.

13:19.880 --> 13:22.170
Oh.
I don't get it.

13:22.170 --> 13:24.080
Aren't you supposed to be
a computer or something?

13:24.080 --> 13:26.420
Can't we just use
a calculator?

13:26.420 --> 13:27.920
Is my dad
not home yet?

13:27.920 --> 13:29.710
No.
He's not.

13:29.710 --> 13:30.830
I'm gonna leave, okay?

13:30.830 --> 13:32.080
Yeah.
Yeah.

13:32.080 --> 13:33.710
Hi.

13:33.710 --> 13:35.080
I have to talk to you.

13:35.080 --> 13:36.620
Right now.

13:36.620 --> 13:45.790
♪♪

13:45.790 --> 13:47.380
What is it?

13:47.380 --> 13:49.500
Okay. I just came from a meeting
at the hospital.

13:49.500 --> 13:51.000
It was about
a clinical trial.

13:51.000 --> 13:53.500
Clinical trial?
Just listen, okay?

13:53.500 --> 13:57.120
They said it was a cure,
but the payment was Piper.

13:58.920 --> 14:01.960
Hold on. I'm sorry.
Uh, what?

14:01.960 --> 14:03.880
Start from the beginning.
Okay.

14:03.880 --> 14:05.830
My doctor, Dr. Reed,
said she knew about this study.

14:05.830 --> 14:07.960
So she set up a meeting
between me and this lady

14:07.960 --> 14:09.500
who knew my entire
medical history --

14:09.500 --> 14:11.250
It was a woman?
Yeah. Yeah, here.

14:11.250 --> 14:13.710
Her name was Helen.
She gave me that number.

14:13.710 --> 14:15.790
That's all I got.

14:15.790 --> 14:17.040
I knew it was
too good to be true.

14:17.040 --> 14:18.580
As soon as she said "cure,"
I knew it.

14:18.580 --> 14:20.080
Chris, I need you to
run a number right now.

14:20.080 --> 14:21.670
Alex: What the hell do they want
with Piper?
212...

14:21.670 --> 14:23.790
Well, they said that this wasn't
the right place for her.

14:23.790 --> 14:26.540
That we wouldn't know how to
handle her or some nonsense.

14:26.540 --> 14:28.790
And pull all the security
footage from the hospital.

14:28.790 --> 14:31.250
Okay.

14:31.250 --> 14:32.540
Did you call this number?

14:32.540 --> 14:33.830
'Course not.

14:33.830 --> 14:37.580
♪♪

14:37.580 --> 14:38.710
[ Line ringing ]

14:38.710 --> 14:40.460
Leave a message.
[ Beep ]

14:40.460 --> 14:41.750
You just made a mistake.

14:41.750 --> 14:43.620
A big mistake.

14:43.620 --> 14:46.750
And I am really gonna enjoy
making you pay for it.

14:46.750 --> 14:52.290
♪♪

14:52.290 --> 14:53.710
Damn.

14:56.000 --> 14:57.330
[ Knock on door ]

14:59.380 --> 15:02.380
Hey.
Sorry to bug.

15:02.380 --> 15:04.080
I'm your neighbor.
Right next door.

15:04.080 --> 15:05.500
Do you know
where the ice maker is?

15:05.500 --> 15:07.290
Oh, sure. It's, uh,
down that way, I believe?

15:07.290 --> 15:08.750
By the, uh,
vending machine.

15:08.750 --> 15:10.330
That's a cool accent.
Thanks.

15:10.330 --> 15:12.040
You from England?

15:12.040 --> 15:14.120
Uh, Welsh.
Close enough.

15:14.120 --> 15:15.960
Are you a journalist?

15:15.960 --> 15:17.000
I think I've read
some of your stuff.

15:19.500 --> 15:22.960
Yeah, and you must be
a, uh, federal agent.

15:22.960 --> 15:26.620
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah. Got me.

15:26.620 --> 15:30.290
Ryan Brooks.

15:30.290 --> 15:31.380
You mind if I come in?

15:31.380 --> 15:33.000
Yeah. I do, actually.

15:33.000 --> 15:35.330
I'm just, uh, in the middle
of working right now.

15:35.330 --> 15:38.000
Sure, sure.
Yeah, I get it.

15:38.000 --> 15:40.000
Uh, seriously, though,
I --

15:40.000 --> 15:43.670
your series on
augmented reality, super cool.

15:43.670 --> 15:45.500
Thanks.

15:45.500 --> 15:48.290
Then I read your profile
of Richard Kindred.

15:48.290 --> 15:51.080
Blowing a little smoke
up his butt, but okay.

15:51.080 --> 15:56.210
And then I -- I read your
article on Chief Jo Evans.

15:56.210 --> 15:58.420
Adopting
a little orphaned girl.

15:58.420 --> 16:00.210
Which I gotta be honest --
kind of threw me.

16:00.210 --> 16:03.210
What's the, uh,
connection there?

16:03.210 --> 16:04.880
No connection.
No?

16:04.880 --> 16:06.500
No.
Just doing a favor for a friend.

16:06.500 --> 16:08.540
Trying to locate
the little girl's family.

16:08.540 --> 16:10.620
That is
really nice of you.

16:10.620 --> 16:13.000
Really nice.

16:13.000 --> 16:15.670
It's -- Um, I've been trying to
get ahold of her,

16:15.670 --> 16:18.120
but she seems pretty busy,
so I thought I'd talk to you.

16:18.120 --> 16:20.290
And you're friends.

16:20.290 --> 16:21.960
I did not know that.

16:21.960 --> 16:23.710
Well, best of luck.

16:23.710 --> 16:26.250
What are you
working on now?

16:26.250 --> 16:28.120
I never like to
talk about a story

16:28.120 --> 16:29.460
until I've written it,
you know?

16:29.460 --> 16:32.040
Well, yeah,
that seems pretty smart.

16:32.040 --> 16:33.880
I totally get it.

16:33.880 --> 16:35.920
Must be
a pretty great story.

16:35.920 --> 16:39.460
[ Cellphone vibrates ]

16:39.460 --> 16:43.460
You know, we are gonna have to
continue this later.

16:43.460 --> 16:46.210
But I'll definitely
see you around, neighbor.

16:46.210 --> 16:51.040
♪♪

16:51.040 --> 16:54.250
[ Line ringing ]

16:54.250 --> 16:55.620
Leave a message.
[ Beeps ]

16:55.620 --> 16:59.080
Yes.
Uh, my name's Alex Evans.

16:59.080 --> 17:02.330
You made an offer
to someone I know.

17:02.330 --> 17:04.080
I'd like to hear more.

17:10.710 --> 17:11.710
Thank you.

17:11.710 --> 17:13.380
Is your name Alex?

17:13.380 --> 17:15.250
Yeah.

17:15.250 --> 17:17.080
That lady's
looking for you.

17:17.080 --> 17:19.710
[ Indistinct talking on TVs ]

17:33.710 --> 17:35.670
Mr. Evans.

17:35.670 --> 17:37.420
Have a seat.

17:39.420 --> 17:41.830
Alright. Who the hell
are you supposed to be?

17:41.830 --> 17:45.040
I think you know
the answer to that.

17:45.040 --> 17:49.290
You know,
people usually just call back.

17:49.290 --> 17:51.790
You said
you wanted to talk.

17:51.790 --> 17:53.670
Let's talk.

17:53.670 --> 18:02.290
♪♪

18:02.290 --> 18:03.670
[ Exhales slowly ]

18:03.670 --> 18:06.040
♪♪

18:06.040 --> 18:07.580
So do you really have
the cure for cancer?

18:07.580 --> 18:09.750
Or is this just a scam?

18:09.750 --> 18:12.040
Not a scam.

18:12.040 --> 18:14.710
What are you gonna
do with her?

18:14.710 --> 18:17.960
Why?

18:17.960 --> 18:20.460
Because I'm asking.

18:20.460 --> 18:23.500
She'll be
where she belongs.

18:23.500 --> 18:24.830
With us.

18:24.830 --> 18:27.500
Right.
Yeah, well...

18:27.500 --> 18:29.420
I saw that creepy-ass
neighborhood

18:29.420 --> 18:30.540
she used to live in,

18:30.540 --> 18:31.920
and I'm gonna tell you
something right now,

18:31.920 --> 18:34.790
I wouldn't want a dog I liked
living there.

18:34.790 --> 18:36.830
That wasn't me.

18:36.830 --> 18:40.170
Don't conflate my efforts with
those of Augur Industries.

18:42.500 --> 18:44.170
She's a one-of-a-kind.

18:44.170 --> 18:46.670
And she'll be treated
as such.

18:46.670 --> 18:49.620
Yeah. She should.

18:51.460 --> 18:53.120
You've grown fond of her.

18:56.080 --> 18:58.290
She is remarkable.

18:58.290 --> 19:02.580
A perfect construction
in an imperfect world.

19:02.580 --> 19:05.620
Her design
was stolen from us.

19:05.620 --> 19:10.080
I only want to provide for her
a safe environment,

19:10.080 --> 19:13.290
surrounded by people
more equipped

19:13.290 --> 19:16.040
to handle
her specific needs.

19:16.040 --> 19:19.750
So she doesn't
harm herself.

19:19.750 --> 19:22.750
Or someone else.

19:22.750 --> 19:25.330
[ Sighs ]

19:25.330 --> 19:28.670
I don't know
what I'm supposed to do next.

19:28.670 --> 19:31.000
It's simple.

19:31.000 --> 19:33.960
Bring her to me.

19:33.960 --> 19:35.920
And save a man's life.

19:35.920 --> 19:41.790
♪♪

19:41.790 --> 19:43.620
Uh, give us a minute.

19:43.620 --> 19:45.080
Yes, sir.
Thanks.

19:45.080 --> 19:48.000
Evening, Ms. Cox.

19:50.210 --> 19:53.620
[ Exhales sharply ]

19:53.620 --> 19:56.330
Well,
I'm gonna be honest.

19:58.210 --> 20:00.670
I am confused.

20:00.670 --> 20:01.830
'Cause I'm thinking

20:01.830 --> 20:04.170
I'm investigating
Richard Kindred's murder,

20:04.170 --> 20:06.710
and I'm like,
"Great idea.

20:06.710 --> 20:09.170
Talk to
Kindred's daughter.

20:09.170 --> 20:10.670
Prime suspect."

20:10.670 --> 20:14.380
Then when I find her --
you --

20:14.380 --> 20:18.120
I also find
the Southold Chief of Police.

20:18.120 --> 20:23.330
And the whole building
explodes.

20:23.330 --> 20:27.000
I just lost someone.

20:27.000 --> 20:28.750
Someone
very important to me.

20:28.750 --> 20:30.830
You lost someone?

20:30.830 --> 20:32.920
Um, not to split hairs,

20:32.920 --> 20:35.710
but you kind of dissolved him
into a smoothie.

20:35.710 --> 20:38.330
I'm not
talking about him.

20:38.330 --> 20:41.540
See...

20:41.540 --> 20:43.290
[ Sighs ]

20:43.290 --> 20:45.830
This is the part
I'm having trouble with.

20:45.830 --> 20:49.210
'Cause Kindred's murder
and bombing Augur,

20:49.210 --> 20:51.420
they seem linked.

20:51.420 --> 20:54.750
I just don't know how.

20:54.750 --> 20:57.960
And I'm thinking you do.

20:57.960 --> 21:00.380
Well,
of course they are.

21:00.380 --> 21:04.000
The people that blew it up
want what my father wanted.

21:04.000 --> 21:07.460
What I wanted.

21:07.460 --> 21:11.290
They want
what everyone wants.

21:11.290 --> 21:13.670
And what's that?

21:17.000 --> 21:20.460
How much has Chief Evans
told you about Piper?

21:24.000 --> 21:25.790
Yeah,
I guess I'm not surprised.

21:25.790 --> 21:27.380
Thanks, Chris.

21:27.380 --> 21:29.380
[ Cellphone beeps ]

21:29.380 --> 21:30.880
Well, the phone number
was Internet-based

21:30.880 --> 21:32.330
and can't be traced.

21:32.330 --> 21:34.790
And the hospital cameras --
all of them --

21:34.790 --> 21:36.920
inexplicably malfunctioned
today.

21:36.920 --> 21:40.290
Ah. Ah, two dead ends
for the price of one.

21:40.290 --> 21:43.330
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

21:43.330 --> 21:45.000
[ Sighs ]
She's good.

21:45.000 --> 21:47.040
Mm.
But not as good as you.

21:47.040 --> 21:48.790
[ Chuckles ]

21:48.790 --> 21:50.790
Thanks, Dad.

21:53.500 --> 21:56.960
[ Sighs ]

21:56.960 --> 21:59.620
I'm really sorry that they tried
to manipulate you that way.

21:59.620 --> 22:01.420
Oh, I'm not.

22:01.420 --> 22:02.960
She showed her hand.

22:02.960 --> 22:04.330
That's a win in my book.

22:04.330 --> 22:06.830
Yeah, but I mean...

22:06.830 --> 22:08.420
a clinical trial.

22:08.420 --> 22:11.040
Oh.
[ Chuckles ] Yeah.

22:11.040 --> 22:13.920
Yeah. Yeah.
I know. I know.

22:13.920 --> 22:16.460
Well, I wasn't gonna
commit to anything

22:16.460 --> 22:18.290
without getting
more information.

22:18.290 --> 22:20.790
I'm gonna
stay out of it.

22:20.790 --> 22:24.000
I just...you know...

22:24.000 --> 22:27.170
You're considering other
options, that's good.

22:27.170 --> 22:29.250
Well, it's not like
I was aiming for it, honey.

22:29.250 --> 22:31.620
They reached out to me,
you know.

22:31.620 --> 22:35.380
Still,
it did get me thinking.

22:35.380 --> 22:37.080
You see
something like Piper.

22:37.080 --> 22:40.040
Something that just seems
completely impossible,

22:40.040 --> 22:42.170
that I never
would've believed

22:42.170 --> 22:45.420
it could happen
in a million years...

22:45.420 --> 22:48.670
You know,
maybe I just don't know

22:48.670 --> 22:52.380
how everything
is gonna end...

22:52.380 --> 22:53.670
maybe.

22:56.620 --> 22:57.880
What?

22:57.880 --> 22:59.250
I'm just happy.

22:59.250 --> 23:00.380
[ Door opens ]
Don't be happy.

23:00.380 --> 23:01.960
I don't want you
to be happy yet.

23:01.960 --> 23:03.040
[ Chuckling ]
It's too late.

23:03.040 --> 23:03.880
No. Don't.
[ Door closes ]

23:03.880 --> 23:06.210
Hey.
[ Chuckles ]

23:06.210 --> 23:08.620
[ Exhales sharply ]

23:08.620 --> 23:11.120
You were right. It worked
hook, line, and sinker.

23:11.120 --> 23:13.420
Hey! Alright. Nice job.
I'm telling you right now.

23:13.420 --> 23:14.710
She bought it.

23:14.710 --> 23:17.290
I am a master
at espionage.

23:17.290 --> 23:18.830
Okay.
So how does this happen?

23:18.830 --> 23:19.880
What --
What happens next?

23:19.880 --> 23:21.420
Um, she said
she's gonna text me...

23:21.420 --> 23:22.920
Okay.
...a time and a place.

23:22.920 --> 23:26.000
She also, um,
gave me this.

23:26.000 --> 23:29.080
Supposed to
put it on her wrist.

23:29.080 --> 23:31.170
I don't know what for,
but...

23:31.170 --> 23:33.380
-Okay.
-Hm.

23:33.380 --> 23:35.750
[ Cellphone vibrates ]
Oh, sorry.

23:37.670 --> 23:39.670
Chief Evans.
Agent Brooks.

23:39.670 --> 23:44.330
Had a productive and, well,
bizarre chat with Emily Cox.

23:44.330 --> 23:45.750
I was gonna file
my official report,

23:45.750 --> 23:47.790
but I wanted to give you
a chance to see it.

23:47.790 --> 23:50.170
Stop by my office tomorrow
if you'd like.

23:50.170 --> 23:55.880
♪♪

23:55.880 --> 24:01.750
♪♪

24:01.750 --> 24:03.750
[ Clears throat ]

24:05.540 --> 24:07.420
Chief Evans?
Yes.

24:07.420 --> 24:09.210
Good morning. I'll take you up
to see Agent Brooks.

24:09.210 --> 24:11.170
Okay. Thank you.

24:14.210 --> 24:16.500
Your firearm will be secure.
This way.

24:16.500 --> 24:23.210
♪♪

24:23.210 --> 24:29.920
♪♪

24:29.920 --> 24:31.790
Chief Evans.

24:31.790 --> 24:33.750
Thank you for coming.

24:33.750 --> 24:35.460
Have a seat.

24:36.880 --> 24:38.620
So you're questioning me
now?

24:38.620 --> 24:41.420
Just talking.
Why don't you sit?

24:41.420 --> 24:43.330
Without a lawyer?

24:43.330 --> 24:45.000
You must think
I'm an idiot.

24:45.000 --> 24:46.380
No, thank you.

24:46.380 --> 24:47.880
I know
you're not an idiot.

24:47.880 --> 24:49.920
And if you want to escalate
things to the next level,

24:49.920 --> 24:51.710
absolutely
get a lawyer.

24:51.710 --> 24:53.460
That's a great line.

24:53.460 --> 24:55.710
I've used that line.
[ Voice recorder beeps ]

24:55.710 --> 24:56.710
This is
Special Agent Ryan Brooks.

24:56.710 --> 24:58.290
The time is 8:07.

24:58.290 --> 24:59.920
You're wasting your time,
Agent Brooks.

25:05.580 --> 25:08.080
I have witnesses that can place
Alan Wilkis at the Peconic Inn.

25:08.080 --> 25:09.500
Staying with
your reporter buddy.

25:09.500 --> 25:11.880
It's not gonna be hard
to connect that to you.

25:11.880 --> 25:16.580
Lying to a federal agent
gets you five years in Danbury.

25:20.460 --> 25:22.210
Am I under arrest?

25:22.210 --> 25:24.330
I'd rather not
play it that way.

25:26.210 --> 25:27.750
Off the record.

25:30.920 --> 25:32.580
[ Voice recorder beeps ]

25:32.580 --> 25:35.040
Off the record.

25:39.880 --> 25:41.330
Where's Alan Wilkis?

25:41.330 --> 25:42.500
I don't know.

25:42.500 --> 25:43.750
Need a better answer
than that.

25:43.750 --> 25:45.290
I don't have one.

25:45.290 --> 25:48.420
[ Sighs ]

25:48.420 --> 25:51.330
I had every intention of
handing him over to the FBI.

25:51.330 --> 25:53.380
After Emily Cox
was off the streets.

25:53.380 --> 25:55.330
He escaped.

25:55.330 --> 25:57.500
It wasn't
your call to make.

25:57.500 --> 25:59.960
Richard Kindred was murdered
in federal custody.

25:59.960 --> 26:03.710
So...I made it my call.

26:07.290 --> 26:09.080
Why was Wilkis
so important to you?

26:11.790 --> 26:14.000
Actually, I already know
the answer to that question.

26:14.000 --> 26:16.170
It's because of Piper.

26:16.170 --> 26:19.620
Emily said Piper is dead.

26:21.880 --> 26:24.080
She's mistaken.

26:24.080 --> 26:26.420
Okay.
She's wrong about that.

26:26.420 --> 26:28.500
Let's see if she's wrong
about this --

26:28.500 --> 26:31.710
is Piper...

26:31.710 --> 26:34.420
not human?

26:34.420 --> 26:36.880
Do you believe that?

26:39.380 --> 26:40.960
Emily does.

26:40.960 --> 26:43.170
And Kindred did.

26:43.170 --> 26:46.880
And I think the people who
blew up that Augur facility did.

26:46.880 --> 26:48.080
They're called Splinter.

26:51.830 --> 26:54.040
But you knew that already.

26:54.040 --> 26:57.330
Because your name is on
every affidavit

26:57.330 --> 27:01.040
and every search warrant request
looking into Splinter.

27:01.040 --> 27:03.290
The FBI's been chasing them
for 15 years.

27:03.290 --> 27:04.880
How do you know
about Splinter?

27:04.880 --> 27:07.790
Because I saw them.

27:07.790 --> 27:12.170
And because they reached out
to my family to make a deal.

27:12.170 --> 27:16.380
They cure
my father's cancer.

27:16.380 --> 27:19.750
And in return,
I hand over Piper.

27:19.750 --> 27:22.710
They reached out to you.

27:22.710 --> 27:24.750
[ Chuckles ]
Splinter?

27:24.750 --> 27:26.210
Some woman named Helen.

27:28.790 --> 27:30.710
[ Sighs ]

27:30.710 --> 27:34.920
She believes that my ex-husband
is handing over Piper.

27:34.920 --> 27:37.330
Tonight.

27:37.330 --> 27:38.790
If you're interested,

27:38.790 --> 27:41.960
we can make this our own little
joint task force.

27:41.960 --> 27:44.670
You get the collar.

27:44.670 --> 27:48.460
And once this is over,
you leave Piper alone.

27:48.460 --> 27:49.620
Hold on. Hold on.

27:49.620 --> 27:52.290
This is happening
in about 12 hours.

27:52.290 --> 27:55.830
You're never gonna
get this opportunity again.

27:55.830 --> 27:57.290
Do we have a deal?

28:00.500 --> 28:03.790
Okay, "Remove from package."

28:03.790 --> 28:06.540
Come on. There we go.

28:06.540 --> 28:08.290
Pairing mode on.
Alright, pairing, pairing,

28:08.290 --> 28:09.620
pairing, pairing, pairing,
pairing, pairing.

28:09.620 --> 28:11.750
Alright, "connecting device."

28:11.750 --> 28:13.920
Bluetooth pairing unsuccessful.
Ugh, come on.

28:13.920 --> 28:15.500
Bluetooth pairing unsuccessful.
[ Groans ]

28:19.210 --> 28:20.920
[ Sighs ]
You know, Piper.

28:20.920 --> 28:25.080
If I can impart one piece of
wisdom to you, it is this --

28:25.080 --> 28:27.380
never buy cheap stuff
online.

28:29.580 --> 28:31.920
Those people said
they could make you better.

28:33.330 --> 28:35.670
Who told you that?

28:35.670 --> 28:37.920
I heard.

28:39.790 --> 28:43.710
Do you have some kind of
super hearing, or something?

28:43.710 --> 28:47.210
No.
Just regular hearing.

28:47.210 --> 28:50.250
Oh...

28:50.250 --> 28:51.960
Don't you want
to get better?

28:51.960 --> 28:54.670
Yeah. Sure I do.

28:54.670 --> 28:57.080
[ Sighs ]

28:57.080 --> 28:59.830
But I would never
trade you for that.

28:59.830 --> 29:01.960
But --
No. No buts.

29:01.960 --> 29:04.790
I didn't even
have to think about it.

29:04.790 --> 29:06.330
You don't have to
think about it, either.

29:06.330 --> 29:07.500
Okay?

29:09.500 --> 29:10.790
Okay.

29:10.790 --> 29:15.290
♪♪

29:15.290 --> 29:17.620
Maybe
I can figure it out.

29:17.620 --> 29:19.830
Figure what out?

29:19.830 --> 29:21.620
How to make you better.

29:21.620 --> 29:23.790
Mm.

29:23.790 --> 29:25.540
Yeah, maybe.

29:25.540 --> 29:28.380
[ Sighs ]

29:28.380 --> 29:31.000
I'll bet you can do
a lot of things.

29:31.000 --> 29:35.290
I'll start thinking
right away.

29:35.290 --> 29:38.920
Okay. [ Chuckles ]

29:38.920 --> 29:42.420
♪♪

29:42.420 --> 29:44.000
Okay.

29:44.000 --> 29:46.540
[ Sighs ]

29:46.540 --> 29:47.960
The good thing about
the ferry landing

29:47.960 --> 29:49.380
is there's only one way
in or out.

29:49.380 --> 29:51.460
I'll watch the entrance.

29:51.460 --> 29:53.120
Yeah. Brooks and I
can cover the parking lot.

29:53.120 --> 29:55.250
Yeah, okay. We'll grab her
as soon as we see her.

29:55.250 --> 29:57.960
She won't get anywhere near you.
Okay?
Sounds good.

29:57.960 --> 29:59.880
Alright, go ahead and clip this
on the back of your waistband.

29:59.880 --> 30:02.460
Uh, Alex Evans,
this is Agent Ryan Brooks.

30:02.460 --> 30:03.920
Hey.

30:03.920 --> 30:06.000
Um, can you get Agent Brooks
hooked up with a two-way?

30:06.000 --> 30:09.170
Uh, yeah. His mic still
needs to be connected.

30:09.170 --> 30:11.000
Okay.
This way.

30:11.000 --> 30:12.170
I got you.

30:12.170 --> 30:13.210
Alright.

30:13.210 --> 30:15.120
Has this been
in someone else's ear?

30:15.120 --> 30:16.920
Um, I don't know.
'Cause if it has,

30:16.920 --> 30:19.290
that's so gross
and not sanitary at all.

30:19.290 --> 30:20.580
Put it in your ear,
okay?

30:20.580 --> 30:22.580
Yeah.
Thank you.

30:22.580 --> 30:23.670
Alright.

30:23.670 --> 30:25.830
I'm gonna be able to hear you
at all times.

30:25.830 --> 30:27.500
[ Sighs ]
How's this?

30:27.500 --> 30:29.210
That's too loose.

30:29.210 --> 30:31.500
It's got to be really tight
or you're exposed.

30:34.880 --> 30:36.330
Okay.

30:36.330 --> 30:38.290
[ Thunder rumbles ]

30:38.290 --> 30:39.710
Yeah. Okay.

30:39.710 --> 30:42.920
Hey. It's okay.

30:44.540 --> 30:46.920
I'm not sure
this is a good idea anymore.

30:46.920 --> 30:49.330
We got to do it.

30:49.330 --> 30:51.620
Yeah.
But there are other ways.

30:51.620 --> 30:52.790
It's not your job to --

30:52.790 --> 30:55.250
I want to do it.

30:55.250 --> 30:58.210
It feels good to finally bring
the fight to them, you know?

30:59.290 --> 31:00.830
It's gonna be good.

31:00.830 --> 31:02.540
Okay.
Alright.

31:02.540 --> 31:04.210
[ Thunder crashes ]

31:04.210 --> 31:12.330
♪♪

31:12.330 --> 31:20.420
♪♪

31:20.420 --> 31:28.500
♪♪

31:28.500 --> 31:30.000
Is this thing working?

31:30.000 --> 31:31.830
Perfectly.

31:31.830 --> 31:33.040
I'm in position, Chief.

31:33.040 --> 31:34.710
Here, too.

31:34.710 --> 31:37.420
Excellent.

31:37.420 --> 31:39.540
Well, guys.
Now that I have your attention,

31:39.540 --> 31:42.620
you will now be listening
to the musical stylings

31:42.620 --> 31:44.880
of Alex Evans
singing "On My Own"

31:44.880 --> 31:46.960
by Patti LaBelle
and Michael McDonald.

31:46.960 --> 31:49.080
I'll be singing both parts.

31:49.080 --> 31:52.210
♪ I'm on my own ♪

31:52.210 --> 31:53.920
♪ Why did it end this -- ♪

31:53.920 --> 31:56.120
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

31:56.120 --> 31:58.080
She's calling.

31:59.500 --> 32:00.790
Hello?

32:00.790 --> 32:03.670
Helen: I'm here.

32:03.670 --> 32:05.330
I don't see you.

32:05.330 --> 32:08.040
To your left.
Near the water.

32:08.040 --> 32:09.960
The boat
with the red light.

32:12.830 --> 32:14.580
[ Cellphone beeps ]

32:14.580 --> 32:17.710
Guys, she wants me to
go down near the boats.

32:17.710 --> 32:20.330
No.
I won't be able to see you.

32:20.330 --> 32:21.880
I got an eyeline.

32:21.880 --> 32:23.210
Okay. Tell us the minute
that you see her,

32:23.210 --> 32:24.250
and we'll move in.

32:24.250 --> 32:25.500
Alright.

32:25.500 --> 32:34.580
♪♪

32:34.580 --> 32:43.920
♪♪

32:48.830 --> 32:50.290
Hey.

32:50.290 --> 32:52.330
Jo asked me to come over
and check on you guys.

32:52.330 --> 32:55.880
So I thought I'd try and buy
your affections with takeaway.

32:55.880 --> 32:58.210
Sold.

33:02.000 --> 33:03.170
Have you heard
anything yet?

33:03.170 --> 33:04.460
Nothing yet. You?

33:04.460 --> 33:06.000
No.

33:06.000 --> 33:07.960
Well [sighs]
I'm sure she's fine.

33:07.960 --> 33:09.540
She's extremely capable.

33:09.540 --> 33:11.750
Yeah. I know that.

33:11.750 --> 33:13.880
I never did
thank you properly

33:13.880 --> 33:15.830
for taking care of me
the night I got injured.

33:15.830 --> 33:18.080
It was never my intention
to put anyone in danger.

33:18.080 --> 33:21.210
Yeah. I know.
You're welcome.

33:24.420 --> 33:25.830
You want a drink,
Piper?

33:25.830 --> 33:27.830
Yes, please.

33:29.210 --> 33:30.750
Are there
any egg rolls?

33:30.750 --> 33:32.500
Yes. Right here.

33:35.670 --> 33:37.290
He used to
not like you.

33:37.290 --> 33:38.540
That's correct.

33:38.540 --> 33:40.420
But now he does.

33:40.420 --> 33:42.830
Well, he loves you guys
very much.

33:42.830 --> 33:44.880
And I can tell
that you love all of them.

33:44.880 --> 33:48.170
I think I do.

33:49.750 --> 33:51.210
But maybe
that's not real.

33:51.210 --> 33:52.330
Yes, it is.

33:52.330 --> 33:54.250
It's as real
as anyone else.

33:54.250 --> 33:56.000
In that way,
you aren't any different.

33:56.000 --> 34:04.170
♪♪

34:04.170 --> 34:06.540
[ Thunder rumbles ]

34:06.540 --> 34:07.750
Jo:
What's going on over there?

34:07.750 --> 34:10.080
A whole lot of nothing.

34:10.080 --> 34:12.210
There's a car here,

34:12.210 --> 34:14.460
but I don't think
anybody's in it.

34:14.460 --> 34:16.620
Alright.
Well, keep your engine running.

34:16.620 --> 34:18.250
Chris, Brooks,
you have anything?

34:18.250 --> 34:19.790
Negative.

34:19.790 --> 34:21.170
Quiet over here.

34:21.170 --> 34:22.670
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

34:22.670 --> 34:24.670
Hold up.

34:24.670 --> 34:27.750
She's calling me.
I'll put it on speaker.

34:27.750 --> 34:28.920
[ Cellphone beeps ]

34:28.920 --> 34:30.500
I'm here.

34:30.500 --> 34:33.620
Helen: Shut the car off.
Leave the lights on.

34:33.620 --> 34:35.330
Where are you?

34:35.330 --> 34:37.500
Please do
as instructed.

34:37.500 --> 34:43.790
♪♪

34:43.790 --> 34:46.040
Very good.
Now step out of the car.

34:46.040 --> 34:48.120
Do not get out of that car,
Alex.

34:48.120 --> 34:49.710
Show me where you are.

34:49.710 --> 34:51.960
Helen: Mr. Evans, you are not
in a position to negotiate.

34:51.960 --> 34:53.290
Okay.
I'm stopping this.

34:53.290 --> 34:54.750
Alex, start the car
and drive away.

34:57.540 --> 34:59.330
I'm getting out.

34:59.330 --> 35:01.380
Alex. Alex!

35:01.380 --> 35:06.830
♪♪

35:06.830 --> 35:10.000
[ Thunder rumbles ]

35:10.000 --> 35:12.330
Alex,
get back in the car.

35:12.330 --> 35:17.170
♪♪

35:17.170 --> 35:18.790
Okay. Show yourself.

35:18.790 --> 35:20.620
Where's the girl?

35:20.620 --> 35:21.670
In the car.

35:21.670 --> 35:23.920
Bring her out.

35:23.920 --> 35:26.460
No, that's not how
we're doing things.

35:26.460 --> 35:29.000
You crawl out from
whatever hole you're in

35:29.000 --> 35:30.580
or I'm taking her home.

35:30.580 --> 35:36.960
♪♪

35:36.960 --> 35:43.420
♪♪

35:43.420 --> 35:44.960
That's you?

35:44.960 --> 35:46.380
What's happening?

35:46.380 --> 35:48.960
She's across the water.
She's on the other side.

35:48.960 --> 35:51.080
What?
Can we get to her?

35:51.080 --> 35:53.420
No. Alex,
get back in the car.

35:53.420 --> 35:55.880
This isn't
what we talked about.

35:55.880 --> 35:57.830
[ Tires squeal ]

35:57.830 --> 35:59.920
She's taking off.

35:59.920 --> 36:01.210
She's taking off!

36:01.210 --> 36:02.710
Does anybody
have eyes on her?
Coming your way.

36:02.710 --> 36:04.580
[ Siren wailing ]

36:04.580 --> 36:07.080
[ Tires squeal ]

36:08.880 --> 36:10.000
I got her.

36:10.000 --> 36:12.830
Chris, get to Alex.

36:12.830 --> 36:14.000
I'm on it.

36:14.000 --> 36:20.460
♪♪

36:20.460 --> 36:27.170
♪♪

36:27.170 --> 36:33.710
♪♪

36:33.710 --> 36:35.750
[ Tires screech ]

36:35.750 --> 36:44.830
♪♪

36:44.830 --> 36:46.540
[ Tires screech ]

36:49.210 --> 36:51.540
Hands up.
Show me your hands right now.

36:51.540 --> 36:54.250
She doesn't belong to you.
She never will.

36:54.250 --> 36:56.290
You've got nowhere to go.
Hands.

36:56.290 --> 36:58.170
You seem very kind.

36:58.170 --> 37:01.420
And I'm sure she's been
well-cared-for with your family.

37:01.420 --> 37:02.580
Get them up.

37:02.580 --> 37:05.330
Don't let
this end badly.

37:05.330 --> 37:08.210
I'm sorry.

37:08.210 --> 37:10.500
Hey. Hey!

37:10.500 --> 37:19.920
♪♪

37:19.920 --> 37:21.830
She just...

37:21.830 --> 37:23.290
Where's Piper?

37:23.290 --> 37:25.250
What?
Where's your family?

37:25.250 --> 37:28.750
At home.
Get them someplace safe.

37:28.750 --> 37:32.920
[ Cellphone vibrating ]

37:32.920 --> 37:35.040
Hey. You okay?

37:35.040 --> 37:36.960
Take them
to the station.

37:36.960 --> 37:38.380
What, now?

37:38.380 --> 37:39.540
Benny. Please.
Just get them to the station.

37:39.540 --> 37:40.420
Okay?
I'll meet you there.

37:40.420 --> 37:42.040
Alright.

37:42.040 --> 37:44.120
Go.

37:44.120 --> 37:45.170
You need to call
Search and Rescue --

37:45.170 --> 37:47.670
Yeah, yeah. Go!

37:47.670 --> 37:52.080
♪♪

38:02.250 --> 38:05.210
[ Police radio chatter ]

38:05.210 --> 38:06.960
Hey, everybody's okay.

38:06.960 --> 38:08.620
In your office.
Thanks, Daph.

38:08.620 --> 38:10.960
Hey. Sorry, guys.
Hey.

38:10.960 --> 38:12.210
Are you okay?

38:12.210 --> 38:13.790
Yeah, honey.
Everybody's fine.

38:13.790 --> 38:15.500
Where's Piper?

38:15.500 --> 38:17.330
What are you
talking about?

38:17.330 --> 38:20.330
Benny said
he was taking her to you.

38:20.330 --> 38:22.580
No, I told him
to bring everybody here.

38:22.580 --> 38:24.960
That's not what he told us,
honey.

38:29.380 --> 38:32.540
Mom...
where's Piper?

38:32.540 --> 38:37.620
♪♪

38:37.620 --> 38:40.080
[ Line ringing ]

38:40.080 --> 38:41.830
We're sorry.
You have reached a number

38:41.830 --> 38:43.710
that has been disconn--

38:43.710 --> 38:45.000
Call the hotel.

38:45.000 --> 38:46.170
Okay.

38:46.170 --> 38:47.330
Everybody make it?

38:48.750 --> 38:50.580
Hey.

38:50.580 --> 38:52.880
What's --
What's wrong?

38:52.880 --> 38:55.080
I don't know
where Piper is.

38:55.080 --> 38:57.920
What do you mean
you don't know where Piper is?

38:57.920 --> 39:01.540
Uh...the hotel said
Benny checked out.

39:01.540 --> 39:03.540
Hours ago.

39:05.120 --> 39:07.540
I-I don't understand.

39:07.540 --> 39:16.000
♪♪

39:16.000 --> 39:18.790
I...

39:18.790 --> 39:20.670
I need you
to put out an APB.

39:20.670 --> 39:23.460
The reporter?

39:23.460 --> 39:25.580
[ Cellphone beeps ]
It's Brooks.

39:25.580 --> 39:27.670
I need to put out a BOLO
on Gallagher, Benjamin...

39:27.670 --> 39:30.620
Hey.
What do we do?

39:30.620 --> 39:37.670
♪♪

39:37.670 --> 39:40.290
We get her back.

39:46.880 --> 39:49.920
[ Angel Olsen's "Impasse"
plays ]

39:49.920 --> 39:57.330
♪♪

39:57.330 --> 40:04.750
♪♪

40:04.750 --> 40:08.710
♪ Go on ahead ♪
I don't like this place.

40:08.710 --> 40:10.290
Yeah, you know what?

40:10.290 --> 40:12.210
Me neither.

40:12.210 --> 40:15.290
But Jo told us
that she would meet us here.

40:15.290 --> 40:17.830
So I'm sure
she'll be here soon.

40:17.830 --> 40:24.710
♪ Take it all out on me ♪

40:24.710 --> 40:26.880
See?

40:26.880 --> 40:28.330
She's here already.

40:28.330 --> 40:31.960
♪ I'm too caught up to see ♪

40:31.960 --> 40:38.790
♪ Everyone will believe ♪

40:38.790 --> 40:42.330
♪ Will believe ♪

40:42.330 --> 40:43.540
♪ Will believe ♪

40:43.540 --> 40:45.620
It's not her.

40:45.620 --> 40:47.170
Drive.

40:47.170 --> 40:48.500
What is that?

40:48.500 --> 40:51.080
That is like...
a light switch.
[ Powering up ]

40:51.080 --> 40:52.620
For you.

40:52.620 --> 40:54.830
To make sure that you don't
accidentally hurt anyone.

40:54.830 --> 40:57.000
Take it off.
It's not forever.
It's just for a moment.

40:57.000 --> 40:59.250
Take it off!
Look,
I know that this is scary.

40:59.250 --> 41:00.670
There's a lot of
explaining --

41:00.670 --> 41:03.080
Piper.
♪ Everyone ♪

41:03.080 --> 41:06.960
♪ Will believe ♪

41:06.960 --> 41:10.580
♪ Will believe ♪

41:10.580 --> 41:12.790
♪ Will believe ♪
Look at you,

41:12.790 --> 41:15.670
running like the devil himself
was chasing you.

41:15.670 --> 41:19.000
But I'm not the devil.

41:20.540 --> 41:23.880
I'm a friend.

41:23.880 --> 41:25.120
♪ Break it down ♪

41:25.120 --> 41:27.250
I wanna go home.

41:27.250 --> 41:29.290
Please let me go home.

41:29.290 --> 41:32.420
Home is not what
you think it is, Piper.

41:32.420 --> 41:34.210
Why?

41:34.210 --> 41:37.080
Listen to me.

41:37.080 --> 41:40.290
Jo has been
very, very good to you.

41:40.290 --> 41:43.120
But she'll never
understand you.

41:43.120 --> 41:45.250
Because
she's not like you.

41:45.250 --> 41:48.670
♪ Don't you, now? ♪

41:48.670 --> 41:52.000
♪ Don't you, now? ♪

41:52.000 --> 41:55.420
Don't be afraid.
♪ Don't you, now? ♪

41:55.420 --> 41:59.080
♪ Don't you, now? ♪

41:59.080 --> 42:02.920
♪ Don't you, now? ♪

42:02.920 --> 42:06.040
♪ Don't you, now? ♪

42:06.040 --> 42:09.500
♪ Don't you, now? ♪

42:09.500 --> 42:19.250
♪ You think this is
what I wanted when I said ♪

42:19.250 --> 42:24.500
♪ I'm just livin' in my head ♪

42:32.750 --> 42:41.210
♪♪

42:41.210 --> 42:49.670
♪♪

42:49.670 --> 42:57.880
♪♪
